# Template

![Coverage Badge][coverage_badge]

<div align="justify">

A [cookiecutter] template for python projects.

</div>

## Quick Start

<div align="justify">

To let `GitHub` automate certain things for you like

- generating your project from the template,
- creating code coverage badges,
- writing changelogs,
- creating releases, and
- publishing docs to `GitHub Pages`

you need to create `Personal Access Token`s to authorize `GitHub` to perform these actions.

</div>

### Create a Personal Access Token

1. Go to your [GitHub account Personal Access Tokens page].
1. Under `Tokens (classic)`, click `Generate new token > Generate new token (classic)`.
1. Set an expiration date and give it the scope of `gist`.
1. Click `Generate token`, copy the value, and save it to a secure location.

    > ⚠️ **NOTE:**  
    >  
    > **You won't be able to see the token again**, so be sure to save it before you close the window. [KeePass] is highly recommended for saving sensitive information.

